The '''Hárskút Wind Farm''' was a wind power project in [[Veszprém (county)|Veszprém County]], [[Hungary]]. It was to have 30 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>[http://www.ebrdrenewables.com/sites/renew/Lists/Projects/DispForm.aspx?ID=721&Source=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eebrdrenewables%2Ecom%2Fsites%2Frenew%2Fcountries%2FHungary%2Fdefault%2Easpx Hárskút Wind Farm]</ref> with a nominal output of 1.5 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] which would have delivered up to 45 MW of power, allegedly enough to power over 18,100 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$60 million.

