A '''near-equatorial orbit''' is an orbit that lies close to the [[Equator|equatorial plane]] of the object orbited.  This orbit allows for rapid revisit times (for a single orbiting spacecraft) of near-equatorial ground sites.{{Fact|date=May 2009}}  

